<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-536-931  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 536 931.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Oct 15 1990 n390 p43(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>To change a leopard's spots.... (Businessland UK reorganization)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pickering, Bobby.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Businessland UK is trying hard to reshape itself, despite the factthat it is among the top five resellers in the United Kingdom.andO;The value-added reseller is attempting to teach its sales forcesome new tricks, because its margins have become paper thin andits profits have sunk.andP;  Staff morale is at a low due to layoffs,the departure of senior management, and branch closures.andP;  Thesales staff is being retrained to support the company's goal ofbecoming a global reselling organization with high-end productofferings.andP;  The salespeople are mostly left over from thebought-out Granada group, which specialized in pushing low-end,stand-alone microcomputers.andP;  The new general manager believes itis not too late to change the organization.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Businessland UK Ltd. (management).andO;Topic:     MicrocomputersMarketing StrategySales ManagementTraining of EmployeesUnited Kingdom.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>